サブクエストテスト[詳細/ショウサイ]１
サブクエストテスト[詳細/ショウサイ]２
サブクエストテスト[詳細/ショウサイ]３
The shifty guy lost a postcard-sized\nkeepsake somewhere on campus.\nHe wants you to find it...
The shifty guy lost his postcard-sized\nkeepsakes somewhere on campus.\nFind all three and report back.
All three keepsakes have been located.\nReport back to the shifty guy on the\nfirst floor of campus.
The keepsakes turned out to be candid\nsnapshots of <FLC:SENNO>, secretly sold around\nschool unbeknownst to the student council.
The grandma who lost her way seems to be\nplaying a mobile game called Mekkemon GO.\nHelp her find her way to the Shopping District.
The grandma who lost her way seems to have\nbeen playing the mobile game Mekkemon GO.\nTake her to the Downtown Shopping District.
The grandma who lost her way was looking\nfor the Mekkemon, Simiape. She's very glad\nthat her in-game cage limit has increased.
The grandma who lost her way is looking\nto catch more rare Mekkemon.\nHelp her find her way to the park by the school.
The directionally-challenged grandma was\nlooking for more rare Mekkemon to catch.\nTake her to the park by the school.
The directionally-challenged grandma was\nhunting the rare Mekkemon, Go-bruh Kobruh.
There seems to be a fake cop in\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA>. If you see someone\nsuspicious, report it to the kindly cop.
The fake cop was only cosplaying the\nprotagonist from an action series.\nReport it to the kindly cop.
You informed the kindly cop of the fake\ncop's true identity... You were advised\nto exercise more caution in the future.
Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> has lost something embarrassing.\nShe wants you to retrieve it from the gym storage...
Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> said she lost something\nembarrassing. Look for it in the gym storage.
The door to the storage room wouldn't\nopen, but you found a squishy plushie.\nInform Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> back on the first floor.
Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> was looking for her plushie of\nthe mascot character, Spooky Bigbums.\nShe is fond of its creepy-cute aesthetic.
That thing just ran right past!\nWe need to chase it down, snap a photo,\nand figure out what it is.
Whoops! The <FUL:UMIBOZU> got away from you...\nReport back to the marine biology club\nmember down by the school road.
The <FUL:UMIBOZU>'s capability for speech is a\nphenomenal discovery for the next seminar.\nThe marine biology club member is chuffed.
The kids say a Dark Society hid\ntheir football somewhere in town.\nThey want you to find it...
The kids said that a "Dark Society" hid\ntheir football somewhere in town.\nHelp them by finding and retrieving it.
The one who hid the football was actually\nthe boy whose foot was injured. He misled\nhis naive friends to avoid falling behind.
The manager of <FUL:TANAKA> Mart is trying to find the\nthief who stole his <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burgers.\nHe wonders if you're interested in catching the thief...
The manager of <FUL:TANAKA> Mart is trying to find the\nthief who keeps stealing his <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burgers.\nSearch for clues nearby.
You've gathered enough clues\nabout the <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burger thief.\nHead to their hiding spot.
The culprits behind the stolen <FUL:UMIBOZUMAN>burgers\nwere a family of hungry stray cats.
A brash kid suggests you might want to stop\nthe man at Seaside Park dressed as a PsyRanger...
A brash kid said he saw a man dressed\nlike a PsyRanger wandering around Seaside Park.\nGo give him a stern talking-to.
You drove off the thugs attacking PsyRed.\nTurns out the old lady he protected was the one who\nriled them up in the first place.
The grandma got lost\nwhile chasing a boss Mekkemon.\nHelp her find her way to the Hospital.
A wayward grandma got lost\nwhile chasing a boss Mekkemon.\nHelp her find her way to the hospital.
She was searching for the boss Mekkemon\nto help her granddaughter with a tough battle.\nLooks like their adventure is just getting started.
A gloomy man asked you to find\nthe raffle tickets he lost.\nHe says he'll give you one if you find them all.
A gloomy man asked you to find\nfour raffle tickets he lost.\nSearch the Downtown area for them.
As thanks for finding them,\nthe man gave you one of them.\nTry your luck at the raffle.
You've gathered all four raffle tickets.\nReport back to the gloomy man in Downtown.
The man traded all his other prizes with you\nfor the C-rank prize he wanted.\nHe then went home with a spring in his step.
She thought you were chasing her,\nbut the misunderstanding has been cleared up.\n<FUL:JOSEPHINE> seems to have a favor to ask...
<FUL:JOSEPHINE> escaped from her owner and (not so\npolitely) insisted you help her escape town.\nTake her to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Station.
At the station, <FUL:JOSEPHINE>'s owner arrived to\ntake her home. Swayed by her charm, <FUL:JOSEPHINE> did\nan about-face and headed back on her own.
A travel InaTuber wants you to show him\naround town. If you don't point out the best spots,\nhe might end up commenting on the worst...
A travel InaTuber asked you to show him\naround town. Start by taking him to\na tourist spot at Seaside Park.
The InaTuber thought the Doll & Finn statues\nlacked pizzazz. Try finding a flashier spot\non School Road.
He wasn't sold on the <FUL:UMIBOZU> statue—said he\nwanted something that really screams <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nTake him to a tourist spot at the Port.
The InaTuber loved the big <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> monument.\nHe even tried to recruit you for his production\nteam, but you politely turned him down.
For various reasons,\na man who couldn't attend his class reunion\nasked you to deliver a letter on his behalf.
A man who couldn't attend his class reunion\nasked you to deliver a letter on his behalf.\nTake it to the reunion at Champon Bluespring.

After you delivered the letter, the reunion
attendees were thrilled to learn it was from their
beloved former teacher. But who sent it remains a
mystery.
A <FLC:RAIKA> fan girl wants to try the exact parfait\n<FLC:RAIKA> had in a photo she saw.\nHelp her find the café where <FLC:RAIKA> went.
A <FLC:RAIKA> fan girl asked to try the exact parfait\n<FLC:RAIKA> had in a photo she saw.\nHelp her find the café where <FLC:RAIKA> went.
The café <FLC:RAIKA> visited was Café Tank.\nAs the strawberry parfait was discontinued\nthe fan girl decided to recreate it herself.
A bossy little boy claims to be a Tristar Elite.\nHe's apparently in trouble and wants your help...
A bossy little boy lost his Tristar Badge\nsomewhere in town. Check the Shopping District,\nthe Old Shipyard, or the park on School Road.
Return the Tristar Badge to the bossy little boy\non <MNT:NAGUMO> Road.
Turns out the boy was pretending to be\na Tristar Elite to cover for a friend who lost the\nbadge. He promised he won't lie anymore.
She thought you wanted to capture her,\nbut the misunderstanding has been cleared up.\n<FUL:JOSEPHINE> seems to have a favor to ask...
<FUL:JOSEPHINE> escaped from her owner and (not so\npolitely) insisted you help her escape town.\nTake her to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Port.
At the port, <FUL:JOSEPHINE>'s owner arrived to take her\nhome. Swayed again by her charm, <FUL:JOSEPHINE> did\nan about-face and headed back on her own.
An ambitious art club member wants you to help\nwith her painting practice. In return,\nshe'll create a promotional poster for you.
An ambitious art club member asked you to help\nher improve. Battle the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Shopkeepers\nand show her some special moves.
Inspired by your special moves, the art club girl\nwhipped up a rather... avant-garde promo poster\nfor the football club.
Your classmate <FLC:HARAGUCHI> asked you to help gather the materials\nthat Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> requested...
Help <FLC:HARAGUCHI> \nClass 1-A, the Archive, and the science lab.
Take the three documents you collected\nto the staff room.

<FLC:HARAGUCHI>'s real goal wasn't gathering documents—
it was to get a pep talk.
But after <FST:RAIKA>'s harsh words,
he seems hooked on her tough love instead.
<FLC:MOJA> from the student council wants you to help\nfind his friend <FUL:SHIROYAMA>. In return,\nhe'll give you something useful for football.
<FLC:MOJA> from the student council wants to see his\nfriend <FUL:SHIROYAMA>. Search for him along Rural Road.
Find <FUL:SHIROYAMA> in a shady spot on Rural Road.
<FLC:MOJA>'s friend <FUL:SHIROYAMA> turned out to be a\nwhite cat who oddly resembles <FLC:SENNO>.
An eager member of the school newspaper wants\nto do an exclusive on the football team.\nIf you agree, he'll help promote your team.
An eager reporter from the school paper asked for\nan exclusive on the football team. Show him your\nintense training at the Hecaton Stairway.
The reporter burned the fiery determination\nyou showed during training into his mind\nand left to write his story.

The school paper staff are debating which photo
to put on the front page.
They want you to demonstrate some saves
and shots in action to see which stands out more.

The newspaper club is arguing over
which photo to feature on the front page.
Show them some top-notch saves and shots
in a match against Seagull FC.
After watching the match, the reporters made up\nand decided to put photos of both the\ngoalkeeper and striker on the front page.
An irritable boy says that the Dark Society has appeared,\nand he wants your help.

The boy says his friends won't come play
football because of the dastardly doings
of the "Dark Society." Talk to his friends
on Rural Road, Downtown, and the Coastal Road.
The boy's friends all clammed up and wouldn't\nsay why. For now, go back to the irritable boy.
Head to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Station and confront the man\nfrom the Dark Society.

The man turned out to be a coach from a
football school in the next town.
The boy's friends were secretly going
there to get better and impress everyone.
An old man who's a fan of dolphins wants\nto see Doll and Finn's signature trick one more time.
An old man said he wanted to see Doll and Finn's\nsignature trick one more time.\nLead him to the Old Shipyard.
Watching <FLC:RAIKA> and <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> train, the old man\njoyfully believed Doll and Finn had been reborn\nas humans and come to visit again.
Fans of <FLC:YAGYU> from the baseball faction\nseem to be planning an attack on <FST:UNMEI>.\nThey want your help to stop it.
Take three photos of <FLC:YAGYU> during the\nTwinford Junior High match and hand them over\nto the <FLC:YAGYU> superfan.
After hearing you out, the baseball faction\nchanged their minds about\n<FLC:YAGYU> returning to their club.
<FFC:MUJURIKI> from the space laboratory wants you\nto find areas with unusual magnetic fields.\nYou do owe him one for the merger...
<FFC:MUJURIKI> from the space laboratory asked you\nto find three areas with unusual magnetic fields\naround the school grounds.
You've located three spots with unusual\nmagnetic fields. Time to report back to <FLC:MUJURIKI>.

The three unusual magnetic field spots formed
a giant delta shape across the school campus.
The space laboratory's goal was
to use it to contact extraterrestrials.
<FUL:TSUKIMI> mentioned that a certain someone\nwants you to taste their noodles again...
Speak with <FUL:TSUKIMI> and\nagree to taste-test the new noodles.
<FST:FUMIO> ran away to hone his noodle-making skills,\naiming to surpass his mother. The <LST:TSUKIMI>\nfamily's bonds grew stronger through this trial.
A strict science teacher aspiring to\nbecome an InaTuber wants to join\none of your training sessions to film a video.
Team up with the strict science teacher aiming\nto be an InaTuber and run the tire target drill.

The teacher's daughter confessed that,
even though she's a fan of <FUL:MAN-TAICHO>,
she cared more about her father.
The teacher swore he'd spend more time with her.
Someone wants you to eat at noodle shops around <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>\nand collect ten Don Gorillo stickers.
Eat at noodle shops around <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>\nand collect ten Don Gorillo stickers.
You've got ten Don Gorillo stickers!\nHand them over to the Don Gorillofan girl\nin the Downtown district.
Turns out the Don Gorillo fan girl's dad\nwas the original creator. When she praised him,\nhe got his confidence back.
An eighth grader who likes older people\nwants you to hear him out.\nHe apparently has a favor to ask...

An eighth grader who worships Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI>
like a goddess wants something of hers for luck.
Ask Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> in the staff room
for one of her belongings.
Take the ballpoint pen she gave you\nand deliver it to the eighth grader\nnear the football club room.

The eighth grader believed the team's winning streak
was thanks to their "goddess of victory,"
Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI>—and just had to have
one of her belongings as a lucky charm.
<FST:MAKINO> seems to be in a bit of trouble\nand could use your help.
<FST:MAKINO>'s late dog Tank's favorite toy was\nswiped by a sneaky cat. Get it back for her.
Bring Tank's rope toy you recovered\nfrom the cat back to <FST:MAKINO>.
Having regained the lost toy,\n<FST:MAKINO> vowed never to lose it again.
A staff trainer said a new recruit hasn't shown up\nand wants you to help finding them.
You were asked to find a blonde,\nglasses-wearing newbie staff member named <FUL:YAMADA>.\nSearch for him in the Football Gardens.
<FUL:YAMADA> was seen escorting a lost child\nnear the management center by the lodging area.\nSearch for him there.
<FUL:YAMADA> wasn't at the management center.\nSearch elsewhere in the Football Gardens.
<FUL:YAMADA> apparently left in a hurry.\nSearch around the Football Gardens for him.
You found <FUL:YAMADA> helping someone\nat the football ground near the lodging area.\nReport back to the staff trainer.
The newbie staff <FUL:YAMADA> was late for roll call\nbut put helping others first.\nHe's a good staff member.
The local kids's leader wants you to show him\na live match at the Back Alley Field.
Take on the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Shopkeepers to show\nthe local kids' leader a match worth watching.
The boy, inspired by <FLA:GARYU>'s moves\nin a match, declared his dream: to become\na top-tier goalkeeper in Football Frontier.
Help the busy event staff\nfind the lost football.
Help the busy event staff find the lost football.
The ball the staff was looking for was\na precious keepsake full of memories.
You seem to have\nquite the connection with <FUL:JOSEPHINE>.\nIt looks like she has another favor to ask...
<FUL:JOSEPHINE> escaped from her owner and (not so\npolitely) insisted you help her escape town.\nTake her to the school's Skyport.

<FLC:AYASHINO> disguised himself as <FUL:JOSEPHINE>'s owner
to get her to open up. Afterward, <FUL:JOSEPHINE>
returned home with her real owner,
their bond stronger than before.
A bubbly reporter from overseas has gotten lost.\nGuide him through the Odaiba Football Gardens.
A bubbly reporter from overseas has gotten lost.\nTake him to the football ground\nby the Lodging Cottages.
Take the bubbly reporter to the Lodging Cottages.
Take the bubbly reporter to see\nthe Statue of <FUL:ENDO>
Take a photo together with the bubbly reporter\nin front of the <FUL:ENDO> statue.
Seeing the <FUL:ENDO> statue reminded\nthe bubbly reporter of the passion he felt\nwhen he first fell in love with football.

You heard a rumor that a junior has been
wandering around at night. Concerned,
someone asks you to check on them.
It seems they've been seen with their grandmother.

<FLC:SHUNTA> from the track and field club
has been wandering around late at night.
Ask around the north campus building,
the school rooftop, and Seaside Park.
<FLC:SHUNTA> was seen with an old lady\nin Seaside Park at night.\nTalk to her for more details.

Caught up in Mekkemon Go, <FLC:SHUNTA> was
spending nights playing with the old lady,
which got him hit with a no-games order
from the track captain.
<FUL:TSUKIMI> wants to talk to you\nand asked if you have a moment.
<FST:TSUKIMI>'s daughter <FFC:CHINAMI> seems to have a stalker.\nGo ask her for details.
<FST:CHINAMI> says she's been feeling watched.\nCheck Hillview Terrace, Rural Road,\nCoastal Road, and the Old Shipyard.
The stalker turned out to be <FUL:KAJI>.\nHe found a pendant <FST:CHINAMI> lost and wanted to\nreturn it—but was too shy to say anything.
A food-loving old man says he'll make\nthe Ultimate Soup to help you\nimprove your football skills...
An old man asked you to gather three kinds\nof wild herbs for his soup. Search the lodging area\nof the Odaiba Football Gardens.
You've collected all three wild herbs.\nTake them to the food-loving old man\nwho is waiting in the Odaiba Football Gardens.
The old man's cooking was called outdated, but\nhe's determined to perfect a new ultimate soup,\nand headed back to his kitchen to do just that.
A rookie security guard claims to have seen\na ghost at night and can't focus on work.\nThey want you to prove that no ghosts are around...
A ghost has been spotted lurking\nin the Odaiba Football Gardens.\nFind an eyewitnesses and uncover its true identity.
A ghostly figure with a hairstyle similar to\nyours was seen drifting and talking around\nthe beach. Head there to investigate.
Rumors say the culprit disguised as\nthe <FUL:UMIBOZU> appears at the beach at night.\nGo there and expose them.
The <FUL:UMIBOZU> of Odaiba was actually Vort-X,\na multifunctional training drone from AI Academy.
Someone wants you to help them by\nasking athletes what foods they like to eat.
Ask three people in the Football Gardens\nwhat foods they'd prefer while working out.
You've gathered plenty of opinions from athletes.\nNow, report back to the pensive woman.
The pensive woman worked at Harborfront Bakery.\nWhile she dreamed up wild new products,\nyou stood firm—classic castella's the best.
A book-loving senior is looking for someone who can lend\nthem a copy of Sigdor's Tale.
Ask around school to find someone who'll\nlend you a copy of Sigdor's Tale.
You borrowed Sigdor's Tale\nfrom a kid deep in reading.\nNow deliver it to the senior bookworm.
It was all a setup to convert someone into a\nSigdor fan. But you were already a true Sigdorian.
A suspicious reporter who claims they've\nnever written a false article wants to interview you.
A shady reporter might be spreading lies.\nReturn to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> and stop him.
The shady reporter has to be at the café.\nHead to Café Tank and confront him.
A man gained success from those fake articles.\nThe shady reporter might be a "Dream Writer"—\nsomeone whose words make reality bend.

<FUL:YOTSUBA>, a transfer student who was once
<FUL:ALICE>'s spy, says he won't return to Royal Academy
until he meets a certain someone. He only saw them once,
and doesn't even know their name or grade.
<FUL:YOTSUBA> is smitten with "that girl." Ask around school\nfor eyewitness reports and find her.
No solid leads yet, but one person comes to mind.\nHead to the Old Gym Storage.
The "girl" <FUL:YOTSUBA> fell for was actually UM-BZ9,\na football training robot built by <FLC:MOMOCHI>.
The wife of a visiting couple\nwants you to get them\na cold drink at the shopping mall.
Grab an ice-cold drink at the shopping mall\nand bring it to the couple.
Wear the CHAMP-ON Limited Top and\ntake a commemorative photo with the man.
The couple was affiliated with CHAMP-ON.\n—they might have just wanted\na photo with the limited jersey.
A veteran chef wants you to tell him\nabout Nagasaki's local dishes\nto help create a new menu item.

A cook needs help creating a new menu
that captures Nagasaki flavors.
Collect three local specialties from the
Chanpon shop, <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Station, and Café Tank.
You've gathered three local Nagasaki specialties.\nDeliver them to the veteran cook in\nthe lodging area of the Odaiba Football Gardens.
The new dish looked strange at first, but the\nfirst bite revealed a comforting, delicious flavor\nthat truly captured the taste of Nagasaki.
My new life at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> begins.\nTime to talk to some nearby students\nand learn more about the school.
I've heard what the students think of <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>\nand learned more through SNS.\nTime to head to my classroom, 1-A.
<FLC:KISOJI> offered to show me around,\nbut even after I said no, he keeps following me.\nI need to shake him.

I passed out protecting <LST:SAKURAZAKI>
and woke up in the hospital.
I'll stop by Seaside Park on the way home
for some fresh air.
I found an old video of <LST:SAKURAZAKI>\nplaying football. I should ask around school\nto find out more about him.
<LST:SAKURAZAKI> is headed the same way as me.\nI'll just take the usual route.
I talked to a few students.\nTime to organize what\nI've learned in my Intelligence Bookmarks.
My classmate, <FLC:KISOJI>, kept on following me around,\nbut it looks like he's finally given up.\nI'll just head home.
I now know more about <LST:SAKURAZAKI>.\nTime to organize what\nI've learned in my Intelligence Bookmarks.
When I'm with <LST:SAKURAZAKI>,\nmy love for football starts to stir again.\nBut I should head on home for now.
I should start an Inacord\ngroup for the three of us.
We're starting a football club, and <FLC:KISOJI>—\nwho says he's got experience—is joining us.\nTime to look for a club room.
